                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15010047" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2015 02:21:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stateful scanners are by definition not REST-ful. We should have deprecated them when stateless scanners were added, in retrospect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Deprecate in 1.x and remove in 2.x? Too sudden?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15010108" author="enis" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2015 03:02:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Deprecate in 1.x and remove in 2.x?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;+1. I think it is fine. 2.0 removes a lot of other stuff in the client APIs anyway. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15010853" author="jon@cloudera.com" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2015 12:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;-1.  Deprecate in 2.0 and keep in 1.x please.  Being more aggressive breaks&lt;br/&gt;
our compat/deprecation story, and unless stock 2.x is wire compat the&lt;br/&gt;
proxies are our shield.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211; &lt;br/&gt;
// Jonathan Hsieh (shay)&lt;br/&gt;
// HBase Tech Lead, Software Engineer, Cloudera&lt;br/&gt;
// jon@cloudera.com // @jmhsieh&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15011322" author="stack" created="Wed, 18 Nov 2015 16:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stateful scanners are by definition not REST-ful.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lol&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Deprecate in 1.x and remove in 2.x? Too sudden?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d say so, this late in the 1.x game. Deprecate in 1.1 and remove in 3.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15018941" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 22:32:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, deprecate only in 1.x branches and on master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
